\begin_layout Standard
\paragraph_spacing onehalf
\noindent
This is in fact an ordinary differential equation composed of scalars 
\emph on
and 
\emph default
vectors - a rather complicated expression with little possibility of obtaining
 an analytical solution.
 However, from Newtonian mechanics the solution must be obtainable since
 complete knowledge of acting forces, along with initial conditions, should
 fully describe particle motion.
 Therefore, a variety of methods do in fact exist to obtain a solution to
 the above expression and are discussed in this chapter.
